General Superintendent of Redemption Ministries Worldwide, Rev. Stephen Akinola has passed away. His death occurred the same day Prophet T.B. Joshua, founder of the Synagogue Church of All Nations (SCOAN) died Joshua died in the wee hours of Sunday morning hours after delivering a sermon. Akinola reportedly underwent a kidney transplant but this is yet to be verified. His congregation and residents have besieged the church, headquartered in Port Harcourt, to pay their last respects. Former Chairman of the Pentecostal Fellowship of Nigeria (PFN), Apostle Eugene Ogu has confirmed Akinolaâ€™s death.